      "title": "Grand Teton Evening Spots",
      "text": "Evenings:\n- Willow Flats Overlook\n- Jackson Lake Dam — sunset picture\n\nSunrises:\n- Schwabacher Landing\n- Barns (Mormon Row)\n- Snake River — sunset",
      "sortOrder": 4
    },
    {
      "title": "Tips from Others' Trips",
      "text": "- Five mile trail hike to Lone Star Geyser (eruption missed by 20 min, but very pretty walk along the river — check if timetable exists)\n- Old Faithful area: erupted at 0907, hiked Observation Peak trail and Solitary Geyser trail, saw Old Faithful again at 1035 and Lion Geyser at 1038. Beehive Geyser erupts every 10hrs to 5 days.\n- Grand Prismatic overlook with 9 mile trail run to Fairy Falls, Imperial Geyser through Fairy Meadows — extra section above Imperial Geyser worth the climb. Bear sightings on the drive.\n- Day 1 reference: Yellowstone Lake, Grand Canyon of the Yellowstone — North Rim Trail & Inspiration Point, South Rim Trail Artist Point to Sublime Point, Sulphur Cauldron, Mud Volcano and Dragon's Breath Spring.",
      "sortOrder": 5
    },
    {
      "title": "Possible Extra Activities",
      "text": "- Grizzly and Wolf Discovery Center in West Yellowstone (90 min each way from Day 2 area)\n- Canoe (lake, river, or canyon?)\n- Covered Wagon experience: https://grgjh.com/rates/",
